<paragraph id="8E8332DB126C1575C4D4DDDE7ACD7BB6" pageId="5" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="603B495C3C349F91D3AD9872E841924F" pageId="5" pageNumber="16">This subgenus can be reliably diagnosed by the shape of anterior margin of pronotum, which is arcuate, and covers the entire head in dorsal view. Also, body shape is elongate (length 3x width), cylindrical and flat; frons is flat; lateral margin of prothorax not widely explanate.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
